1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:02,878
Anton, I tried to make you believe me.

2
00:00:02,962 --> 00:00:05,214
You gave up while I made myself blind...

3
00:00:05,297 --> 00:00:06,716
because I wanted
to get you back from them.

4
00:00:06,799 --> 00:00:09,343
Get me back from who?
Tell it to me straight.

5
00:00:09,427 --> 00:00:10,803
You'll get me back from who?

6
00:00:13,889 --> 00:00:15,099
You know?

7
00:00:24,817 --> 00:00:26,777
No fighting, no drama...

8
00:00:26,861 --> 00:00:29,363
We'll forget about our problems.

9
00:00:29,447 --> 00:00:31,073
I was looking for the kite.
Where did you put it?

10
00:00:31,157 --> 00:00:32,867
Shoot, I think I left it at home.

11
00:00:32,950 --> 00:00:34,452
I should've just taken it myself.

12
00:00:34,535 --> 00:00:36,787
Jackie, let's not fight over a mere kite.

13
00:00:36,871 --> 00:00:37,705
So I'm in the wrong?

14
00:00:37,788 --> 00:00:41,333
I am. I know that kite
means something else to you.

15
00:00:41,417 --> 00:00:42,585
You're just using Eli.

16
00:00:42,668 --> 00:00:44,712
And I know that
you won't run out of reasons

17
00:00:44,795 --> 00:00:47,214
to get mad at me so you could
finally leave me, right?

18
00:00:47,298 --> 00:00:49,216
-Eli's gone.
-Eli!

19
00:00:50,676 --> 00:00:52,595
Your mother saw me with another woman.

20
00:00:52,678 --> 00:00:54,555
When you did that,
did you even think about us?

21
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:55,598
Do you want to know the truth?

22
00:00:55,681 --> 00:00:57,099
Ask your mother, then.

23
00:00:57,183 --> 00:00:59,226
Ask her about her and Sam's relationship!

24
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:13,384
Whatever that was, it's over.
I ended it, Jackie.

25
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:16,178
You only ended it because you got caught.

26
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:20,641
Jackie...

27
00:02:21,225 --> 00:02:23,435
When I get back, you better be gone.

28
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:27,481
-Jackie, please!
-Don't touch me!

29
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:33,320
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

30
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:36,115
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

31
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:38,659
My baby...

32
00:02:40,327 --> 00:02:42,621
Mama's here.

33
00:02:45,374 --> 00:02:47,459
Hold on, okay?

34
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:55,759
I'm sorry.

35
00:03:14,153 --> 00:03:15,112
Jackie.

36
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:19,158
Maybe we can still talk
about what happened.

37
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:21,869
What did Sam tell you?

38
00:03:25,581 --> 00:03:27,041
What does she know?

39
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:32,671
Sam didn't tell me anything.

40
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:36,050
I saw you myself,

41
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:39,178
so there's nothing left to talk about.

42
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:47,645
I really don't know why I did that.

43
00:03:50,648 --> 00:03:54,151
You don't need to explain.
I don't care anymore.

44
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,528
All I care about now is my child.

45
00:03:56,612 --> 00:04:01,075
Because if anything happens to him,
I'll never forgive you.

46
00:04:17,466 --> 00:04:19,760
-What does that mean, Doc?
-Initiate epinephrine.

47
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:22,096
Jackie.

48
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:23,931
Eli! Eli! Eli!

49
00:04:25,349 --> 00:04:26,934
-Jackie.
-Doc, what's going on?

50
00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:28,978
-Jackie.
-Let go of me.

51
00:04:29,061 --> 00:04:30,187
Don't do this!

52
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,773
Fight, Eli, please!

53
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:36,360
Please don't leave me!

54
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:37,569
Eli!

55
00:04:44,326 --> 00:04:45,285
Doc, we've got a pulse.

56
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:55,212
We've got a heartbeat.

57
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:18,652
Jackie, are you all right?

58
00:05:20,362 --> 00:05:22,698
What are you doing?
Did your doctor release you?

59
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,535
Those are just your things. Go home.

60
00:05:27,578 --> 00:05:29,580
I don't need company here.

61
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:31,623
If anything happens, there are nurses.

62
00:05:31,707 --> 00:05:34,293
-Jackie, I can watch over you--
-I don't want that.

63
00:05:36,170 --> 00:05:38,172
Go home.

64
00:05:38,255 --> 00:05:41,050
Every time I see you, my chest tightens.

65
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,926
That's why I don't want you here. Go home.

66
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:45,012
-Jackie, you can't be alone.
-Just go home already!

67
00:05:45,095 --> 00:05:47,139
-Go home!
-I'll stay with you!

68
00:05:47,222 --> 00:05:48,599
-Go home!
-Jackie, please!

69
00:05:48,682 --> 00:05:49,933
Go home!

70
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,834
Sit down first.

71
00:06:29,515 --> 00:06:31,141
Was I wrong?

72
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,520
Was what I did wrong?

73
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:42,820
Everything's still fresh. You're angry.

74
00:06:44,071 --> 00:06:46,323
You're worried about Eli.

75
00:06:55,249 --> 00:06:56,667
It'll pass soon.

76
00:06:58,252 --> 00:06:59,670
I don't know...

77
00:07:00,546 --> 00:07:04,550
Every time I see him,
I see my child's condition.

78
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:09,179
Especially those seconds
when he lost his pulse.

79
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:13,100
Sam, all I felt was anger.

80
00:08:01,356 --> 00:08:02,941
From Anton.

81
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:08,405
Accept it, he tried.

82
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:10,908
I didn't say anything.

83
00:08:13,452 --> 00:08:19,499
There's diapers, milk,
and vitamins for you too.

84
00:08:26,131 --> 00:08:27,925
Is he sleeping well?

85
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:34,014
Are they both asleep?

86
00:08:37,059 --> 00:08:39,311
-I'll help you.
-No, I got it.

87
00:08:39,394 --> 00:08:41,563
I got this, he already
made you the messenger.

88
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:43,232
I'm just folding laundry.

89
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:45,025
I can do it.

90
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:48,445
Not there. There.

91
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,874
Jackie, I know...

92
00:09:02,668 --> 00:09:06,338
you're still angry, but maybe...

93
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:11,260
maybe it's good if he knows
his place in the kids' lives.

94
00:09:13,512 --> 00:09:14,888
He has a place.

95
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:20,394
He's their dad. That won't change.

96
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:25,065
Not just as their father,

97
00:09:25,607 --> 00:09:28,902
but as your partner in life too.

98
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:34,283
Jackie, this isn't one person's job.

99
00:09:34,366 --> 00:09:38,287
Look at your light, it's flickering.

100
00:09:42,332 --> 00:09:43,500
What happened?

101
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:49,965
I've got it.

102
00:09:50,048 --> 00:09:51,383
-Me. I got it.
-No.

103
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:53,218
-I've got it.
-No, I'll do it.

104
00:09:53,302 --> 00:09:55,387
Jackie, come on.

105
00:09:56,138 --> 00:09:58,056
Sit down, okay?

106
00:09:58,140 --> 00:10:01,435
Even for a few minutes,
just so you can breathe.

107
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:22,331
Eli...

108
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,046
Mr. and Mrs. Carpio.

109
00:10:38,347 --> 00:10:40,098
What were the results?

110
00:11:02,454 --> 00:11:04,456
Will our child be deaf?

111
00:11:04,539 --> 00:11:07,376
But Doc, aren't there other options?

112
00:11:07,459 --> 00:11:09,336
This isn't permanent, right?

113
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:12,214
Aren't there things we can do?

114
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:15,217
There are treatments,
interventions, Doc, right?

115
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:31,983
But your child's hearing
cannot be restored.

116
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:34,588
Your apologies won't help, Anton.

117
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:41,553
We need to be strong for Eli.

118
00:12:47,642 --> 00:12:50,270
Jackie, give me a chance.

119
00:12:51,146 --> 00:12:52,689
I'll make it up to you.

120
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:57,027
I'll make it up to Eli.
I'll make it up to our kids.

121
00:12:57,569 --> 00:12:58,737
Jackie...

122
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:03,325
I don't want to waste my life blaming you.

123
00:13:11,166 --> 00:13:13,376
Eli needs both of us.

124
00:13:18,924 --> 00:13:20,842
Our kids need us too.

125
00:13:24,638 --> 00:13:27,224
Things might never be the same again,

126
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,687
but one thing's for sure,

127
00:13:36,942 --> 00:13:39,569
the kids are waiting for you to come home.

128
00:13:49,246 --> 00:13:50,664
Isn't he cute?

129
00:13:51,915 --> 00:13:55,085
Papa, your seminar's over!

130
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:02,801
Can I?

131
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,100
Jackie, thank you.

132
00:14:11,851 --> 00:14:14,479
I'll never waste the chance you gave me.

133
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:20,902
Um, hungry?

134
00:14:24,823 --> 00:14:25,865
Anyone want a snack?

135
00:14:28,702 --> 00:14:30,036
I'm gonna go whip something up.

136
00:14:46,761 --> 00:14:48,555
Jackie. Jackie.

137
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:50,849
Son.

138
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:54,102
Regarding gene therapy,

139
00:14:54,769 --> 00:14:57,772
this might be good
for improving Eli's hearing.

140
00:14:57,856 --> 00:14:59,899
-Read it.
-Mm, okay.

141
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:02,193
I'll read it when I have time.

142
00:15:02,777 --> 00:15:03,862
Don't you have time now?

143
00:15:05,989 --> 00:15:06,823
No, I don't.

144
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:11,453
I don't want to give it
time today, tomorrow,

145
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:13,204
or the following days, Anton.

146
00:15:14,748 --> 00:15:16,541
We tried a lot of things,

147
00:15:16,625 --> 00:15:19,210
but none of them worked.

148
00:15:19,294 --> 00:15:20,337
It's exhausting.

149
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,881
Maybe we can take a break.

150
00:15:22,964 --> 00:15:24,674
Yes, I know that.

151
00:15:24,758 --> 00:15:28,094
I'm just saying, maybe we can still
fix Eli while he's still young.

152
00:15:28,178 --> 00:15:29,304
"Fix Eli"?

153
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:31,222
He's not broken.

154
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:16,059
Mama.

155
00:16:22,357 --> 00:16:23,900
How do you say "Daddy?"

156
00:16:25,902 --> 00:16:29,030
Mama, join us too.

157
00:16:29,114 --> 00:16:30,824
Now that everybody's here,

158
00:16:31,366 --> 00:16:33,576
we have Daddy, Mommy,

159
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:36,663
this is what you call a family.

160
00:16:41,668 --> 00:16:42,585
That's it!

161
00:16:44,713 --> 00:16:45,547
Eli...

162
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:51,761
It will light up
when someone rings the doorbell.

163
00:16:51,845 --> 00:16:54,389
That way, Eli will know
if there's someone outside.

164
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:59,227
Sam, thank you.

165
00:17:00,812 --> 00:17:05,525
I'm sorry for accusing you
of telling on me to Jackie.

166
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:07,277
You even helped us patch things up.

167
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:14,117
You are a good friend.

168
00:17:15,243 --> 00:17:17,954
I'm sorry I let my thoughts
get the best of me.

169
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:20,457
Forget about it, okay?

170
00:17:22,959 --> 00:17:24,210
Especially Eli.

171
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:27,213
Thank you.

172
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:30,592
-Are the kids resting already?
-Yes.

173
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:32,302
I bet they're tired.

174
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:34,220
Yes, but they enjoyed the session.

175
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:40,268
Thank you.

176
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:44,564
Is that right?

177
00:17:46,274 --> 00:17:47,400
That's right.

178
00:18:35,907 --> 00:18:38,034
-I love you.
-I love you.

179
00:18:43,206 --> 00:18:46,376
Matteo said he is able to hear music.

180
00:18:48,711 --> 00:18:49,963
Okay, come here.

181
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:13,194
Mama, come join us and sing.

182
00:19:13,278 --> 00:19:14,195
Did you feel it?

183
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:30,712
You don't seem okay.

184
00:19:34,382 --> 00:19:35,842
Is it that obvious?

185
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:42,640
I haven't slept well lately.

186
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:48,104
Maybe you need this.

187
00:19:51,566 --> 00:19:52,984
It might help you.

188
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:55,612
You'll get a good night's sleep
and feel calm.

189
00:19:57,405 --> 00:19:59,198
You're crazy!

190
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:02,285
Come on.

191
00:20:04,162 --> 00:20:04,996
Sam...

192
00:20:07,665 --> 00:20:09,334
Why do you have that?

193
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:16,549
It's just...

194
00:20:28,686 --> 00:20:30,730
My mother had just died...

195
00:20:33,274 --> 00:20:38,029
and Dad was starting to get sick.

196
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:40,281
Plus, my brother...

197
00:20:41,324 --> 00:20:44,285
Well, I had no one to depend on.

198
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:51,626
There are days when taking them

199
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:55,254
is the only thing that helps me
get through the day.

200
00:21:01,803 --> 00:21:05,181
But lately, I don't think
I need it anymore.

201
00:21:09,018 --> 00:21:10,478
but I feel a lot better now.

202
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:27,870
Through Eli and my other students.

203
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:38,006
That's good to know.

204
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:42,760
Hey.

205
00:21:44,929 --> 00:21:48,016
I'm here if you need someone to talk to.

206
00:22:01,446 --> 00:22:02,321
As for me...

207
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:06,534
I feel like I'm always overthinking.

208
00:22:06,617 --> 00:22:08,202
It's because of Anton.

209
00:22:11,289 --> 00:22:12,790
You know what?

210
00:22:12,874 --> 00:22:15,543
He tried to make a move
on me again last night.

211
00:22:21,966 --> 00:22:24,177
I can't bring back how we used to be.

212
00:22:31,225 --> 00:22:32,226
You see...

213
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:36,022
I used to think

214
00:22:36,564 --> 00:22:39,317
that I couldn't live without him.

215
00:22:42,653 --> 00:22:46,240
But now, no matter how hard I try
to bring my old feelings back...

216
00:22:49,243 --> 00:22:50,453
they're gone.

217
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:58,878
Sometimes, I wonder
if we're doing the right thing.

218
00:23:01,589 --> 00:23:05,176
We're together as parents,
but not as husband and wife.

219
00:23:08,054 --> 00:23:10,515
I think you're both doing good.

220
00:23:11,849 --> 00:23:13,810
Your kids still have no idea.

221
00:23:17,897 --> 00:23:20,691
But Anton often oversteps his boundaries.

222
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:24,946
Especially when the children are around.

223
00:23:26,656 --> 00:23:30,326
Sometimes, I can't help
but show my discomfort,

224
00:23:31,327 --> 00:23:34,580
even if it's just a kiss on the cheek.

225
00:23:36,415 --> 00:23:37,917
I can't hide it.

226
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:56,519
But instead of dwelling on that,
I want to focus on Eli.

227
00:23:57,311 --> 00:23:58,521
Yeah.

228
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:01,732
I want to hear him...

229
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:05,278
and understand him more,

230
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,197
just like how you understand him.

231
00:24:10,074 --> 00:24:13,369
I wonder if there's a way

232
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:15,621
to know what Eli's world feels like.

233
00:26:36,929 --> 00:26:38,764
Pia asked me to do an errand for her.

234
00:26:38,848 --> 00:26:40,182
I have things to do.

235
00:26:43,853 --> 00:26:44,812
I have to go.

236
00:28:52,815 --> 00:28:53,899
Hi.

237
00:28:56,610 --> 00:28:59,029
Do you remember Professor Ramos?

238
00:28:59,113 --> 00:29:01,657
We teased him to treat us
on his birthday, right?

239
00:29:02,992 --> 00:29:04,493
He said yes.

240
00:29:07,872 --> 00:29:09,790
Okay, all right then.

241
00:29:12,001 --> 00:29:14,712
Oh, I have to finish
checking these papers.

242
00:29:17,173 --> 00:29:20,634
We won't take long,
probably just 30 minutes.

243
00:29:20,718 --> 00:29:22,803
Besides, it's free food. Come on.

244
00:29:28,851 --> 00:29:29,935
What's wrong, Sam?

245
00:29:30,019 --> 00:29:33,606
Remember the grant request
we submitted to the mayor

246
00:29:33,689 --> 00:29:34,773
for the Able Hearts Foundation?

247
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:38,444
He approved it.
The grant has been approved!

248
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,613
Oh, my god, Sam!

249
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:16,232
Let's go?

250
00:30:35,668 --> 00:30:36,544
Did you spend time together?

251
00:30:37,169 --> 00:30:38,379
Where's Jackie?

252
00:30:38,462 --> 00:30:39,630
She went straight home.

253
00:30:40,381 --> 00:30:44,009
I'll be the one to take Eli for now,
even in the coming days.

254
00:30:49,723 --> 00:30:51,850
Enjoy, son.

255
00:30:52,643 --> 00:30:53,852
Okay.

256
00:30:54,812 --> 00:30:56,814
All right, thanks. I'll get going.

257
00:31:49,992 --> 00:31:51,869
Are you and Teacher Sam fighting?

258
00:31:57,750 --> 00:31:59,251
Why would you ask that?

259
00:32:00,169 --> 00:32:01,462
Nothing.

260
00:32:02,421 --> 00:32:03,547
It's just that...

261
00:32:04,256 --> 00:32:07,009
You don't take Eli there as often anymore.

262
00:32:07,718 --> 00:32:10,888
And she doesn't visit here
that much either.

263
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:15,100
And I noticed at school,
you're not together anymore.

264
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:19,229
Oh, of course not.

265
00:32:19,313 --> 00:32:20,606
We're just busy.

266
00:32:29,031 --> 00:32:30,616
Jackie, is it true?

267
00:32:30,699 --> 00:32:34,161
I only found out from my niece
who's a nurse at EMC.

268
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,288
Sam's father already passed away.

269
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:46,715
What do you mean…

270
00:32:46,799 --> 00:32:48,926
Wait, when did it happen?

271
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:51,553
Just yesterday.

272
00:32:51,637 --> 00:32:53,722
You were actually
the first person I thought of.

273
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:55,891
Let's go together
if you're going to visit.

274
00:33:00,187 --> 00:33:01,939
I'm going to see Sam now.

275
00:33:04,274 --> 00:33:05,401
Pia.

276
00:33:05,484 --> 00:33:08,654
Take care of what I'm cooking.
It's almost done anyway.

277
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:10,989
When your father arrives,
go ahead and eat.

278
00:33:11,073 --> 00:33:12,783
Don't wait for me, okay?

279
00:33:17,371 --> 00:33:18,497
Sam?

280
00:33:22,251 --> 00:33:23,293
Sam.

281
00:33:28,674 --> 00:33:29,925
I went to the hospital.

282
00:33:32,136 --> 00:33:34,388
I also went to the funeral home, Sam.

283
00:33:36,014 --> 00:33:36,849
His…

284
00:33:37,558 --> 00:33:39,351
I was the one who had his barong cleaned.

285
00:33:39,435 --> 00:33:42,104
The last one he wore.
I should know where that is.

286
00:33:42,187 --> 00:33:44,106
Here! Here!

287
00:33:44,690 --> 00:33:45,899
Here it is.

288
00:33:47,735 --> 00:33:48,944
Where's the handkerchief?

289
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:50,237
Where did he put his handkerchief?

290
00:33:50,320 --> 00:33:52,406
He can't be without one.
He has a favorite handkerchief.

291
00:33:53,115 --> 00:33:56,243
-Sam--
-Where is it? And his shoes?

292
00:33:56,326 --> 00:33:57,327
Sam!

293
00:33:57,411 --> 00:33:58,287
Sam.

294
00:34:07,087 --> 00:34:08,088
Hey.

295
00:34:12,342 --> 00:34:14,386
He told me...

296
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:18,182
he was just going on a vacation.

297
00:34:19,183 --> 00:34:21,643
Why did he leave me?

298
00:34:22,352 --> 00:34:25,606
Why did he leave me?

299
00:34:25,689 --> 00:34:27,191
I don't know anymore.

300
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:31,695
Who can I run to now?

301
00:34:31,779 --> 00:34:33,197
I'm here, Sam.

302
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:35,866
I'm here.

303
00:34:35,949 --> 00:34:37,201
I'm right here.

304
00:34:43,999 --> 00:34:45,918
I'm here.

305
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:35,175
Drink some water.

306
00:35:42,933 --> 00:35:44,726
They were on their way back from Baguio...

307
00:35:49,189 --> 00:35:50,816
He was taken straight to the hospital.

308
00:35:52,985 --> 00:35:56,154
I didn't tell you because things
have been kind of...

309
00:35:57,364 --> 00:35:59,616
awkward between us lately.

310
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:01,368
I just didn't get around to mentioning it.

311
00:36:03,787 --> 00:36:05,789
But thank you for coming to see me.

312
00:36:08,458 --> 00:36:10,544
I want to be here by your side.

313
00:36:22,139 --> 00:36:23,724
You're just sad.

314
00:36:27,227 --> 00:36:29,313
This isn't just because I'm sad.

315
00:36:36,653 --> 00:36:38,906
I've been feeling this
for a long time, Jack.

316
00:36:43,327 --> 00:36:44,578
But you have a husband.

317
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:46,455
You have a family.

318
00:36:48,123 --> 00:36:49,708
A family I care about too.

319
00:37:17,444 --> 00:37:19,947
I don't understand
what I'm feeling either.

320
00:37:23,283 --> 00:37:25,327
I know myself.

321
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:31,333
Wherever I look, wherever I go...

322
00:37:32,167 --> 00:37:33,001
it's you.

323
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:35,128
You're all I think about.

324
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,797
You're all I remember.

325
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:40,258
This is the first time I've felt this.

326
00:37:42,469 --> 00:37:43,971
And I don't…

327
00:37:44,846 --> 00:37:47,057
I don't understand
why it had to happen now.

328
00:37:52,604 --> 00:37:54,606
So it's not just in my head?

329
00:38:02,739 --> 00:38:04,825
But that doesn't mean--

330
00:38:04,908 --> 00:38:07,369
I know. I know. I know.

331
00:38:08,453 --> 00:38:10,622
I don't want to lose you in our lives.

332
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:19,047
I'm not going anywhere.

333
00:38:21,842 --> 00:38:23,427
As your friend.

334
00:38:42,904 --> 00:38:44,114
Here's your coffee.

335
00:38:47,117 --> 00:38:50,662
You know, I'm really sad
that you're leaving.

336
00:38:57,044 --> 00:38:59,046
But it's fine because...

337
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:04,968
I'm glad you accepted
the offer from the other university.

338
00:39:06,762 --> 00:39:09,139
It's a good opportunity for you.

339
00:39:11,808 --> 00:39:13,935
I told you I wouldn't leave.

340
00:39:18,899 --> 00:39:21,193
You don't have to apologize, Sam.

341
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,488
I should.

342
00:39:28,492 --> 00:39:30,786
I was the one who was unfair...

343
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:36,208
between the two of us, actually.

344
00:39:40,796 --> 00:39:42,589
I know that I love you.

345
00:39:50,263 --> 00:39:51,765
I'm happy when I'm with you.

346
00:39:54,518 --> 00:39:56,186
I'm content being with you.

347
00:40:07,322 --> 00:40:09,032
That feeling...

348
00:40:11,493 --> 00:40:13,662
I can't feel it whenever I'm with Anton.

349
00:40:16,790 --> 00:40:18,333
Or with anyone else.

350
00:40:29,177 --> 00:40:30,387
You know what?

351
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:35,016
I chose to leave...

352
00:40:36,810 --> 00:40:38,687
not because I love you.

353
00:40:44,025 --> 00:40:47,529
I chose to leave
because I know you love me.

354
00:41:05,839 --> 00:41:07,757
I know you don't want that either, do you?

355
00:41:25,358 --> 00:41:30,614
While I'm here in Escondido,
we can still be okay, right?

356
00:41:34,576 --> 00:41:35,410
Right?

357
00:41:48,298 --> 00:41:49,132
Friends.

358
00:43:19,681 --> 00:43:21,057
Let's talk outside.

359
00:43:22,517 --> 00:43:24,894
Jackie might come anytime.
I don't want to make a scene.

360
00:43:26,896 --> 00:43:28,857
What are you doing here?

361
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:31,234
Do you think I don't know
there's something going on

362
00:43:31,318 --> 00:43:32,235
between you and Jackie?

363
00:43:34,112 --> 00:43:35,363
I know.

364
00:43:36,489 --> 00:43:38,450
You're in a relationship with my wife.

365
00:44:17,781 --> 00:44:19,074
Talk about shameless.

366
00:44:19,157 --> 00:44:21,284
How could you make a fool out of me?

367
00:44:22,077 --> 00:44:23,578
Are you going to steal my wife from me?

368
00:44:25,288 --> 00:44:26,331
Anton...

369
00:44:27,415 --> 00:44:30,585
I have no plans of
stealing Jackie from you.

370
00:44:38,093 --> 00:44:39,469
But don't worry.

371
00:44:41,763 --> 00:44:43,056
We talked already.

372
00:44:45,183 --> 00:44:46,393
As you should!

373
00:44:48,186 --> 00:44:49,813
Because if not...

374
00:44:51,481 --> 00:44:53,983
I don't know what I might do to you, Sam.

375
00:45:07,580 --> 00:45:09,374
You're really a jerk, aren't you?

376
00:45:17,715 --> 00:45:20,385
Is that what you need to
stay away from my family?

377
00:45:21,094 --> 00:45:22,095
You bastard, Anton!

378
00:45:25,306 --> 00:45:27,016
If I'm a bastard, so be it!

379
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:28,977
Stay away from my family.

380
00:45:29,894 --> 00:45:31,604
Stay away from Jackie...

381
00:45:32,981 --> 00:45:34,524
before I end up killing you.

382
00:45:37,527 --> 00:45:40,780
Don't tell Jackie or
anyone else about this.

383
00:45:40,864 --> 00:45:44,075
Because if you do,
I'll ruin your name to everyone.

384
00:45:44,909 --> 00:45:46,619
Especially with Eli.

385
00:46:03,887 --> 00:46:06,473
Sorry, I just had to tuck Eli in bed.

386
00:46:06,556 --> 00:46:08,725
But I'm on my way now.

387
00:46:10,226 --> 00:46:11,895
I should be the one saying sorry.

388
00:46:14,397 --> 00:46:15,440
A quick change of plans.

389
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:18,610
Okay, then.

390
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:24,073
Are you all right?

391
00:46:24,157 --> 00:46:25,992
You sound different.

392
00:46:27,994 --> 00:46:29,913
But let's just reschedule, okay?

393
00:46:31,706 --> 00:46:34,584
Maybe after Eli's session?

394
00:46:36,461 --> 00:46:38,963
Okay. By the lighthouse.

395
00:46:41,674 --> 00:46:42,550
Okay.

396
00:46:44,093 --> 00:46:45,803
All right. Take care.

397
00:47:00,652 --> 00:47:02,278
Hm? You going out?

398
00:47:03,696 --> 00:47:04,739
No.

399
00:47:19,420 --> 00:47:20,630
Sam.

400
00:48:37,498 --> 00:48:39,250
I just didn't like...

401
00:48:42,337 --> 00:48:44,297
that the last time we talked…

402
00:48:46,924 --> 00:48:50,678
would be our last goodbye.

403
00:49:00,772 --> 00:49:01,898
Me too.

404
00:49:09,906 --> 00:49:12,283
After tomorrow's event,

405
00:49:15,745 --> 00:49:17,121
I'm leaving.

406
00:49:34,931 --> 00:49:36,432
Jackie.

407
00:49:41,437 --> 00:49:42,897
Bye, Sam.

408
00:51:17,450 --> 00:51:19,035
Go. Go.

409
00:51:23,539 --> 00:51:24,791
Jackie...

410
00:53:47,767 --> 00:53:49,852
Your papa and I...

411
00:53:52,480 --> 00:53:53,981
We've been separated.

412
00:53:56,734 --> 00:53:58,069
For a while now.

413
00:54:02,365 --> 00:54:04,992
But that's not an excuse to cheat on him!

414
00:54:05,076 --> 00:54:07,995
That's not an excuse
to fool your children!

415
00:54:08,079 --> 00:54:09,914
Don't raise your voice at your mother.

416
00:54:14,335 --> 00:54:15,419
Oh, right.

417
00:54:16,921 --> 00:54:18,172
Of course.

418
00:54:19,298 --> 00:54:21,175
Because you're both cheaters.

419
00:54:21,258 --> 00:54:22,385
Pia.

420
00:54:22,969 --> 00:54:24,637
Don't talk like that.

421
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:26,681
Don't forget that
we're still your parents.

422
00:54:26,764 --> 00:54:28,140
Really, Pa?

423
00:54:28,224 --> 00:54:29,558
We forgot?

424
00:54:30,810 --> 00:54:31,894
Or did you?

425
00:54:34,522 --> 00:54:38,609
Did you even consider
how we'd feel if you separated?

426
00:54:38,693 --> 00:54:39,902
Yes!

427
00:54:43,990 --> 00:54:45,241
We did.

428
00:54:47,493 --> 00:54:50,663
A thousand times, we did.

429
00:55:06,262 --> 00:55:07,513
Really?

430
00:55:11,892 --> 00:55:13,185
So, that's why.

431
00:55:15,396 --> 00:55:18,232
That's why you were devastated
when Teacher Sam died.

432
00:55:21,277 --> 00:55:22,903
So, that's how much you love her.

433
00:55:27,533 --> 00:55:28,743
What?

434
00:55:29,744 --> 00:55:31,954
Do you regret choosing us?

435
00:55:38,836 --> 00:55:40,087
No.

436
00:55:42,048 --> 00:55:43,507
I don't know.

437
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:50,890
I don't know how to explain it to you.

438
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:54,894
Whatever it is that Sam and I had,

439
00:55:56,312 --> 00:55:57,563
I don't know.

440
00:56:00,357 --> 00:56:02,193
But just to be clear,

441
00:56:04,361 --> 00:56:06,155
we didn't have a relationship.

442
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:08,699
Even though...

443
00:56:11,243 --> 00:56:13,287
Even though I really loved her.

444
00:56:18,250 --> 00:56:22,505
I've never felt that kind of love before.

445
00:56:25,299 --> 00:56:27,510
That's why I don't know how to explain it.

446
00:56:29,428 --> 00:56:31,847
But I am sure of one thing.

447
00:56:31,931 --> 00:56:33,307
It never...

448
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:36,936
crossed my mind to replace you.

449
00:56:39,146 --> 00:56:43,150
Because you kids are
the most important thing in my life.

450
00:56:44,735 --> 00:56:46,862
I could lose anything else.

451
00:56:47,613 --> 00:56:50,282
Just not you.

452
00:57:01,001 --> 00:57:03,546
Just admit that you put yourself first.

453
00:57:05,214 --> 00:57:07,133
That's why you gave up on Papa.

454
00:57:13,097 --> 00:57:15,307
You know what I think is true?

455
00:57:18,269 --> 00:57:20,688
If Teacher Sam were here,

456
00:57:21,647 --> 00:57:23,440
you would've chosen her.

457
00:57:27,069 --> 00:57:29,738
It was a good thing she died!

458
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:31,657
Pia...

459
01:00:45,768 --> 01:00:47,936
Were you...

460
01:00:48,020 --> 01:00:53,525
at the lighthouse

461
01:00:53,609 --> 01:00:55,152
that night?

462
01:00:57,071 --> 01:00:58,280
Were you?

463
01:01:01,742 --> 01:01:03,786
Pia? Pia, where are you?

464
01:01:06,121 --> 01:01:06,997
Pia!

465
01:01:08,123 --> 01:01:08,957
Pia, come on.

466
01:01:09,041 --> 01:01:10,501
Why are you letting her drink,
you bastard?

467
01:01:10,584 --> 01:01:13,045
You're the reason why she's a mess.

468
01:01:15,381 --> 01:01:17,383
-Mr. Carpio!
-Where was she?

469
01:01:17,466 --> 01:01:19,468
She was in town with that kid, Kyle.

470
01:01:19,551 --> 01:01:21,845
You've changed ever since
you hung out with Kyle.

471
01:01:23,889 --> 01:01:25,766
Is this what Anton wanted
to get from you earlier?

472
01:01:25,849 --> 01:01:28,685
-Who owns this?
-If we tell people,

473
01:01:28,769 --> 01:01:31,897
if we tell everyone what happened,

474
01:01:31,980 --> 01:01:34,316
it will bring a scandal to our family.

475
01:01:34,400 --> 01:01:36,610
What about Eli?
What will happen to our kids?

476
01:01:36,693 --> 01:01:39,363
No one should know
about this, Jackie. No one.

477
01:01:39,446 --> 01:01:41,448
Do you understand, Jackie?
